Boston Beer Appoints Jonathan N. Potter as Its CMOHomeMailNewsSportFinanceCelebrityStyleWeatherAnswersFlickrMobileMoreYahooSearchSearchSign inUK Markets open in 5 hrs 32 minsFTSE 1007,443.01-9.31 (-0.12%)FTSE 25019,879.43+116.77 (+0.59%)AIM985.07+1.43 (+0.15%)Boston Beer Appoints Jonathan N. Potter as Its CMOGabriel KaneMarket Realist28 June 2016ReblogShareTweetShareKey Events in the Consumer Sector in the Fourth Week of June(Continued from Prior Part)Price movement Boston Beer Company (SAM) rose by 0.99% and closed at $161.02 per share at the end of the fourth week of June 2016. The stock’s weekly, monthly, and YTD (year-to-date) price movements were 0.99%, 0.27%, and -20.3%, respectively. This means that Boston Beer is trading 1.6% above its 20-day moving average, 1.5% above its 50-day moving average, and 15.7% below its 200-day moving average.Related ETFs and peersThe Vanguard Extended Market ETF (VXF) invests 0.05% of its holdings in Boston Beer. VXF tracks a market-cap-weighted version of the S&P Total Market Index, excluding all S&P 500 stocks. VXF’s YTD price movement was 0.03% on June 24, 2016.The iShares Russell 2000 ETF (IWM) invests 0.15% of its holdings in Boston Beer. IWM tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US small-cap stocks. The index selects stocks ranked 1,001–3,000 by market cap.The market caps of Boston Beer’s competitors are as follows:Constellation Brands (STZ) – $31.1 billionMolson Coors Brewing Company (TAP) – $21.2 billionCompania Cervecerias Unidas S.A.-ADR (CCU) – $4.0 billionBoston Beer’s new CMO Jonathan N. Potter has been appointed as Boston Beer’s CMO starting in August. Potter will oversee its planning and development. He will also be in charge of the execution of brand development, marketing, and advertising initiatives.Performance in fiscal 1Q16Boston Beer reported fiscal 1Q16 net revenue of $188.8 million—a fall of 5.4% compared to net revenue of $199.5 million in fiscal 1Q15. The company’s gross profit margin and operating income fell by 2.8% and 49.3%, respectively, in fiscal 1Q16—compared to the same period the previous year.Its net income and EPS (earnings per share) fell to $7.0 million and $0.53, respectively, in fiscal 1Q16—compared to $13.7 million and $1.00, respectively, in fiscal 1Q16.Boston Beer’s cash and cash equivalents fell by 45.8% and its inventories rose by 9.2% in fiscal 1Q16—compared to fiscal 4Q15. Its current ratio fell to 1.8x in fiscal 1Q16—compared to 2.0x in fiscal 4Q15.ProjectionsThe company made the following projections for fiscal 2016:EPS of $6.50–$7.30gross margin of 51%–53%effective tax rate of ~37%depletion and shipment percentage change of -4%–2%capital spending of $50 million–$70 million to support future growth and product innovation and to drive efficiencies and cost reductionsIn the next part, we’ll look at Kellogg Company.Continue to Next PartBrowse this series on Market Realist:Part 1 - Who Were the Outliers in the Consumer Space at the End of June?Part 3 - Kellogg Establishes Venture Capital to Invest in StartupsPart 4 - Why Did Coca-Cola Invest in Aloe Gloe?ReblogShareTweetShareRecently ViewedYour list is empty.What to read nextAldi's £10 gin has officially been ranked one of the best in the worldHouse BeautifulDid You Know These Stars Have a Baby Together?ZimbioSponsoredChris Grayling seeks to reassure U.S., airlines of Brexit plansReutersUK will not accept chlorinated chicken to secure U.S. trade deal - ministerReutersAmazon sales surge, but spending bites into profitAFP15 Cancer Causing Foods You Probably Eat Every DayPrevention PulseSponsoredP&G reports better results as it fends off activist challengeAFPIreland to spend around 80 billion euros in new 10-year capital plan, PM saysReutersQueen's Speech in 90 secondsReal Life Giants You Won't Believe Actually ExistTurnPagerSponsoredAn entire Scottish island is on sale for just £325k - but it has a disturbing pastSamsung Electronics' record earnings see it overtake AppleAFPEuropean stocks struggle as Wall Street marches onAFPSee Brandy's New Look - Try Not To CringeStantonDailySponsored12 countries with the most positive influence on global affairs9 giveaways that your home is hopelessly outdatedhomify










